  "prompt": "How can I start a t-shirt business online without buying a lot of inventory?",
  "response": "There are several ways to start a t-shirt business online with minimal upfront inventory investment:\n\n1. Print-on-Demand (POD) Services\n- Use platforms like:\n- Printful\n- Printify\n- Redbubble\n- TeePublic\n- Merch by Amazon\n\n2. Dropshipping Model\n- Create designs\n- Partner with POD companies\n- They handle printing and shipping\n- You earn a profit margin on each sale\n\n3. Online Marketplaces\n- Set up shops on:\n- Etsy\n- Shopify\n- Zazzle\n- Society6\n\n4. Social Media Marketing Strategies\n- Use Instagram, TikTok, Facebook\n- Create engaging design content\n- Build a following\n- Drive traffic to your online store\n\n5. Design Considerations\n- Create unique, trendy designs\n- Focus on niche markets\n- Use graphic design tools like Canva\n- Consider hiring freelance designers\n\n6. Low-Cost Marketing\n- Use social media advertising\n- Create engaging content\n- Leverage influencer partnerships\n- Use targeted hashtags\n\n7. Initial Investment\n- Minimal startup costs\n- Pay only when items are sold\n- Focus on design and marketing\n\nThese methods allow you to start with low risk and potentially scale your business.",
